text.en_US: What do we do!?!
He's not responsive. It's like he completely crashed.
How did it even happen?
Heeeeyyy!!!\. Can you hear us?
Wasn't he working on something related to \c[3]hit-stun\c[0]?
I don't know!\. He was already like this when I arrived.
What do we do?\. We can't just go report it on the official channels.
We'll need to try to reproduce and debug the issue ourselves.
Any idea where to even begin?
Nope.\. None at all.

message.en_US: You there!\. Have you seen this bug before?
[shakes head]
We think it has something to do with \c[3]hit-stun overload\c[0].
He was working on modding some attack properties, and we found him like this.
It's hard to tell if he is even still online or not.\. His game is probably crashed right now.
\c[3]Hit-stun overload\c[0], huh?
That player is causing very heavy strain on the servers.
I wonder how this could have happened.
Although with these troublesome modders, who knows what they have been doing to the game files.
I'll have to check if QA is aware of this issue.
This could be a big problem if it becomes widespread.
Isn't that...\! ..!
Lea!\! If this bug can be found by mere modders, it might already be becoming well-known!
We need to hurry!\. If \c[3]Sidwell\c[0] gets wise to this, he might fix the vulnerability!
Whatever you are doing here can wait!\. We need to proceed with the plan before it is too late!
Isn't that the hit-stun overload glitch?
[nods]
I'm surprised that modders of all people managed to discover it too.
This little area they've built must also be derived from an old version of the game servers.
I don't think we need to worry about this being used for a DDoS attack in the official areas since it has been fixed.
Although this poor player here will be stuck like that until they do a full server restart.
This is why you shouldn't mess with files you don't understand!

Can't you just turn the settings off?

message.en_US: I figured out a way to make custom signs.

text.en_US: Wow, so these are all the quests in the entire game?
Not all of them. Just the ones that don't have proper unlock prerequisites.
I'm nowhere near Basin Keep on my account. So I can just go start the quests early?
Technically, but you'd have to find a way to reach Basin Keep early.
I wonder why some late-game quests don't have unlock conditions?
To be fair, it's not normally possible to see all the quests in one place like this so early.
